# A cold resolve runs cmake (build dir appears). After dropping the build dir and reloading (which clears sbt's
# in-session state; the action cache persists on disk), re-resolving the config is a cache hit - cmake does not
# rerun, so the build dir is not recreated.
> Compile/snxConfig
> assertBuilt
> removeBuild
> reload
> Compile/snxConfig
> assertCached

# Editing a vendored source changes its content hash, so the cache key changes and the next resolve is a miss -
# cmake reruns and the build dir reappears.
$ copy-file changes/answer.c vendor/answer/answer.c
> reload
> Compile/snxConfig
> assertBuilt
